      "text": [
        " « إِسْمَاعِيلُ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ لِأَنَّ اَللَّهَ عَزَّ وَ جَلَّ ذَكَرَ قِصَّتَهُ فِي كِتَابِهِ ثُمَّ قَالَ «۝ وَ بَشَّرْنٰاهُ بِإِسْحٰاقَ نَبِيًّا مِنَ اَلصّٰالِحِينَ ۝» »."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2278 - Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) was asked about who the \"sacrificed one\" (Dhabih) was, and Imam (as) said:\n\"Isma'il (as), because Allah (swt), the Mighty and Majestic, mentioned his story in His Book and then said: 'And We gave him glad tidings of Ishaq, a prophet from among the righteous.'\" (Surah As-Saffat 37:112)"
        ]
      }
    },
